Integument
. Body color brown. Body surface and pteromorphs foveolate (diameter of foveolae up to 
6
) and densely microgranulate (diameter of granules less than 
1
). Pteromorphs with distinct wrinkles. Genital plates with one long, longitudinal striae in lateral part. Anogenital region with two lateral, transversal striate bands (
s
), which are located between genital and anal apertures, and one arcuate striate band, which is located posteriorly to anal plates and marginally in ano-adanal region.
